name: Cocaine Usage, USA, 2002-2004
description: The map is based on a survey/report from the Office of Applied Studies of Substance Abuse and Mental Health Service Administration (SAMHSA) of CDC. The percent users by poulation is compiled over three years survey (2002, 2003 and 2004).  Since much of the data is from State agencies, the underlying geographic unit varies from one state to the other. For eg., Ohio collects data at Board level, Massachusetts by census tract, Wash DC by wards. 5/2007http://www.samhsa.gov/
